subject: Oops! I meant How does one express nasalized vowels in Quikscript
msgSnippet: I made a bloomer in my last posting. I meant how does one express nasalized vowels in Quikscript? I intended to send essentially the same message to the yahoo
messageBody:
I made a bloomer in my last posting. I meant how does one express
nasalized vowels in Quikscript?

I intended to send essentially the same message to the yahoo
shawalphabet group, asking how does one express ch, ll and nasalized
vowels in Shavian, and then a modified form to this group asking how
one can express nasalized vowels in Quikscript. I mentioned Quikscript
in the message to the Shawalphabet group to show that Quikscript has
an advantage over Shavian, and to urge them to come up with something
similar in respect of ch and ll, in addition to coming up with a
solution for nasalized vowels.

While I was typing it up, someone distracted me, and I got mixed up,
and sent the message intended for the shawalphabet group to this one.
Since I posted it directly to the group (from the "Post" link, and not
by email) I don't have a record of the posting till it appears on the
site. So I don't know for now exactly what mistake I made! In future,
I will post from my yahoo mailbox.

Cossy
